600,000 people failed to exchange their driver's license
600,000 drivers missed the deadline to exchange their old driving licence, which expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when you can apply for the exchange so that the authorities can manage to issue a new driving licence by the end of the year.
However, the ministry does not fear that after New Year, hundreds of thousands of drivers will go on the roads without valid driving permission.
According to the authorities, mainly those who no longer want to drive have not changed their driving licences.
