The city administration produces around 2000 customers every day.
You have to stand for about half an hour.
In Prague, about 140000 drivers have not yet changed their driver's license.
The exhibition of a new driver's license lasts 20 days.
But it is possible to apply for the exhibition with a shorter period of five days.
In this case, however, the driver must add 500 crowns.
From January onwards, drivers who fail to make the required exchange by the end of the year and who leave without a valid driver's license will face a fine.
The culprit pays a maximum of 2,000 crowns.
However, the police can also leave it with an admonition in the event of an offence.
In the event of an infringement, the penalty may rise to 2500 crowns.
According to previous information, even the one who does not drive at all may get a penalty imposed by the community.
It was said that he could face a penalty of as much as 30,000 crowns.
The ministry already called on the offices to act mildly and impose a maximum penalty of 1000 crowns.
However, according to the spokesman for the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, no one is threatened with a thousand kroner penalty.
The driving licence was a document in which everyone could decide whether he wanted to own it or not.
It was not an identity card that everyone, a valid one, had to have.
People who don't want to drive anymore should hand over their license.
It is sufficient to take him to the competent municipal office or send him there by registered mail.
At the end of the year, driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 became invalid.
However, drivers have to gradually exchange other types of driving licences.
People with driving licences from 1994 to 2000 still have three years to exchange.
The validity of driving licences issued between 2001 and 2004 expires in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, this is about 2.6 million more driving licences.
