Congress agrees with the MIFID directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting, which ended its session today with the Senate Congress resolution on the additional/amendment proposals relating to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
