Which insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, the time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even harder to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, one must be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which determines that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to present the corresponding severance compensation amount in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which consists of several factors, including age, gender, the time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance undertakings set their prices in accordance with the statistics, so that, in the event of a higher risk of accidents, they will also have to pay higher contributions.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women need to make less contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the enterprises, they tend to fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver also has to study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
We now list at this point the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance policy in order to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25s encounter numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and young driving licences.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a comprehensive with deductible, so that the benefits of a comprehensive insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, main representative of Spain at First Europa, a brokerage company for online insurance.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage to the own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hands to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction of the basic rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in the above rates.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its revenues.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to enter into a contract. This is due to the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for a comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, either in the event of an accident or at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who has no children to take out a comprehensive insurance policy; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person permits it.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are regarded as customers with the lowest accident rate, and therefore their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the case that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy, which only begins for the third year of the vehicle, is recommended.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to make a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs, which require a thorough selection, which corresponds to our personal situation.
